Maintainer: Maria Eduarda da Cruz Justino <eueduardacruz@gmail.com>
Description: Provides functions for fitting and analyzing simplex
    regression models with either fixed or parametric mean link functions.
    The package implements the simplex probability density function,
    cumulative distribution function, quantile function, random number
    generation, and variance evaluation. It also offers several fixed and
    parametric link functions for the mean submodel, tools for residual
    analysis and diagnostic plotting, hypothesis testing procedures, and
    influence measures such as Cook’s distance and leverage (hat values).
    In addition, the package includes the Scout Score (SS) criterion for
    model selection, enabling comprehensive inference and diagnostic
    analysis within the simplex regression framework.
